other_tests.findings: The appendix is dilated with wall thickening and adjacent fat stranding, measuring up to 8 mm. Within the proximal lumen of the appendix is a calcified appendicolith. There is no adjacent fluid collection or evidence of extraluminal gas to suggest perforation. The remaining pelvic loops of bowel appear unremarkable. The uterus, adnexa, distal ureters, and bladder are within normal limits. No pelvic or inguinal lymphadenopathy is seen. There is no pelvic free fluid.
